	   <tr><td colspan=2>Simple directions to get your Aegis of Life.<br>Go to SK find skele ruins.  The Putrid Skele that spawns and does not fall to the ground is the PH for Grimrot and is opposite of Ghanex's spawn point.  To get the Undead Grimrot to spawn you kill the PH at 7 AM game time, for the live Grimmy kill the PH at 7PM.  The PH has a spawn time of 3 hours 5 minutes real time so be ready to wait.  You need the Decaying heart off of the undead Grimrot and the Lore No Drop Pestilence scythe off off the live one.  You may have to kill them a couple of times to get the items.  I got lucky and got both in 17 hours of camping.  Once you have both items haul yerself to Qeynos and hit the bank to get some gold.  I converted 100pp at a time to gold and gave it to Lashun Novashine in the cleric guild for faction adjustments.  If you do not have the cash I suggest doing some of the smaller quests, bone chips etc.  It took about 400pp for me to get enough faction (Indiferent to Uberwarmly).  You know your faction is good enough when you go to the head cleric in the flying saucer and ask him about Lord Grimrot. He will answer you and ask you if you are ready to defend life or some such.  Say that you are and if he gives you the quest you have good enough faction.  If he says that is only for our most trusted members, go turn in more gold 2gp at a time to Lashun. When your faction is high enough give the head Cleric both the No Drop Lore Scythe and Decaying heart at the same time.  Congorats! You get your Aegis.  The only lame thing about it is the Superior heal is realy a single charge and so far I have not figured out a way to recharge it, but who knows.  FYI Undead Grimrot is about level 30 and live is a nasty level 35 SK so watch out!<br><br>Update: post con patch... so and so considers you an ally is good enuf for the quest so no more guess work at your faction.<br>&nbsp;<br>Arcturion Dragoran<br>Paladin Extraordinare<br><br>Luuke Skywakka<br>Ubermonk <br>